  "prompt": "What does \"last activity\" mean on Skype?",
  "response": "In Skype, \"Last activity\" refers to the most recent time a user was active on the platform. This indicator helps you understand when a contact was last online or engaged with Skype. Here's a breakdown of what \"Last activity\" typically signifies:\n\n1. **Last Online Time**: It shows the last time the user was connected to Skype. For example, it might display \"Last activity 2 hours ago\" to indicate that the user was online two hours prior.\n\n2. **Recent Interactions**: If a user has recently sent or received messages, made a call, or performed any other interaction within Skype, the \"Last activity\" timestamp may reflect that specific action.\n\n3. **Status Changes**: When a user changes their status (e.g., from \"Online\" to \"Away\" or \"Do Not Disturb\"), the last activity timestamp updates to reflect the time of that change.\n\n### Privacy Considerations\n\n- **Privacy Settings**: Skype allows users to manage their privacy settings, which can affect how their \"Last activity\" is displayed to others. Users can choose to hide their last seen time or appear offline even when they are active.\n\n- **Selective Visibility**: Depending on individual privacy preferences, some users might restrict who can see their last activity. This means that only certain contacts can view this information based on the user's privacy settings.\n\n### How to Check \"Last Activity\" on Skype\n\n1. **Desktop or Web App**:\n   - Open Skype and navigate to your contacts list.\n   - Hover over or click on a contact's name.\n   - You'll typically see their current status (Online, Away, etc.) along with the \"Last activity\" time if they're not currently online.\n\n2. **Mobile App**:\n   - Open the Skype app on your smartphone or tablet.\n   - Tap on the contact you want to check.\n   - The \"Last activity\" information will often appear below their name or within their profile section.\n\n### Important Notes\n\n- **Accuracy**: The \"Last activity\" timestamp is only as accurate as the last interaction the user had with Skype. If a user has the app open but is inactive, it may still show their last activity time based on when they were last active.\n\n- **Updates and Changes**: Skype periodically updates its features and interface. While the \"Last activity\" feature has been a standard part of Skype for years, its appearance and functionality might change with new updates. For the most up-to-date information, it's a good idea to consult Skype's official [Support Page](https://support.skype.com/).\n\n### Conclusion\n\n\"Last activity\" on Skype provides valuable information about when a contact was last using the platform. It helps users determine the best times to reach out and understand the availability of their contacts. However, privacy settings play a crucial role in how this information is shared, ensuring users have control over their visibility on the platform.\n\nIf you have specific concerns or need further assistance with Skype's features, consider visiting Skype's [Help and Support](https://support.skype.com/) resources or contacting their customer support for detailed guidance.",
